**Clarifying git command issues**

I think I made a mistake with the `git diff --stat` command syntax, treating `--stat` as part of the pathspec instead of as an option. It printed a full diff, which wasn’t what the user wanted. I need to ensure that the tool’s output doesn’t include previous tasks that are not relevant. I'll check line numbers with Select-String and explore whether the command `git diff --stat -- <files>` is the right approach. I also need to consider handling CRLF correctly.
**Focusing on code refinement**

I shouldn't output the full diff here. It might be best to improve the regex in my code and focus only on the changed scope. After patching, there shouldn't be any icon characters in the `src/renderer` files, except for the UI text. I’m considering using a script to identify classes that may be responsible for icons. Also, I should check if the `rect` in `icons.tsx` requires a fill, since the icon SVG has a fill of none. Additionally, a refined character scan seems like a good plan!
